retrieveSignals

public RawSigDetectEvent retrieveSignals(java.lang.String terminal,
                                         int num,
                                         javax.telephony.media.Symbol[] patterns,
                                         javax.telephony.media.RTC[] rtcs,
                                         java.util.Dictionary optArgs)
                                  throws javax.telephony.media.MediaResourceException
Retrieve up to num signals from the signal buffer associated with terminal, waiting until either then number of signals is available, a patterns is met, a rtc is fired to stop retrieving, or a timeout occurs.

Note that currently this implementation does not wait for signals to arrive.

Parameters:
terminal - The terminal name to retrieve patterns from
num - The maximum number of signals to return
patterns - A set of signals that cause the call to return early.
rtcs - A set of run-time controls to control the signal detector.
optArgs - Optional signal detector arguments.
Returns:
An event factory that holds the detected signals and any reasons.
